Full Description: GoalShare is an entirely new social networking concept. Through its primary concepts of goal sharing and accountability, GoalShare focuses on the future aspirations of its users rather than past and present experiences like current social networks. Because of this and several other proprietary features highlighted below, GoalShare is largely complementary versus competitive to the current social networking space.  The GoalShare network has four primary user groups: individuals, companies, foundations and events. Users are linked together when they choose to “follow” other users through calendar synchronization, a proprietary and primary feature of each profile page on the social network. Calendar synchronization facilitates goal sharing between users – it allows a user to track on his calendar the progress of goals set by all users he chooses to follow. Thus, not only can users follow and share the progress of goals, but they are held accountable in achieving those goals by their followers through the goal sharing concept. Scott and the other Members feel accountability is not only helpful but essential in achieving goals.

It can cause loss of productive work, inability to enjoy leisure activities and, in time, lead to frustration, anxiety and secondary depression. Get the best back pain treatment in Houston from Dr. Benoy and his professional team will take care of your back pain Dr. EdCheril Benny is an accomplished Neurologist with both international and national experience. Dr Benoy V. Benny is a nationally recognized Spine and Musculoskeletal Medicine Physician. He is Board certified in Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation with fellowship training in Spine and Sports Medicine. He is also involved in the research side as well continuing to publish papers in the field. He is very involved in The International Spine Intervention Society (ISIS) as member of the research committee and is also involved in other societies like the American College of Sports Medicine, Academy of Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation, North American Spine Society. He continues to teach at the Baylor College of Medicine to residents and fellows and is the Director of the Fellowship in Intervention Spine, Sports and Pain Medicine. Whether you take 5, 10, or 20 medications ScopiaRx helps you, your caregivers, and your providers make sure those treatments are safe for you. The idea for ScopiaRx came to Dr. Jeffrey Huth while helping a family member manage her 12 different prescriptions. Like millions of patients, the number of her prescriptions kept creeping up to address new chronic conditions and symptoms. One day, a tipping point was reached, and she just did not feel well.  Jeff has a deep background in both the science and clinical considerations of medication safety. Despite this, it literally took him hours of work to look up all of the information for 12 medications and compare that to the specific traits of one patient. What he also discovered was that there are millions of case reports about side effects from people just like his family member, but that none of this information was at the finger tips of the doctors who were prescribing her medications.  The message was clear. Patients are routinely being prescribed 10, 15, and even 20 medications without a thorough evaluation of drug safety. Why is this happening? It is because physicians and pharmacists do not have the tools that would allow them to do this complicated risk evaluation in the short amount of time that they have with a patient.   For the next five years, Jeff developed a method to put all of this safety and clinical information together in such a way that a computer program could do what takes a trained clinician hours to accomplish. During his work in hospitals and clinics, he talked to fellow physicians and pharmacists about their struggles with drug safety management for complex cases. They discussed numerous product ideas and came up with the core features of ScopiaRx

Full Description: Vermont Hills Family Life Center (VHFLC) has been providing quality childcare and family support throughout the Portland Metropolitan area since 1979, catering to the Portland, Beaverton, Banks, Hillsboro, and Milwaukie regions. We currently operate as one of the most extensive local nonprofit childcare providers, servicing over 30 school sites with 1,400 combined preschool and school age children.  At VHFLC, we enrich children's lives by providing preschool, aftercare, and summer camp environments that are secure, accommodating of all developmental stages, and respectful of each child's unique ability to experience fun, wonder, and challenge. Our teachers meet on a weekly basis to create fun and well-rounded curriculums, focusing on character-building, critical thinking, and interpersonal skills. Activities also emphasize creative expression and physical health.  VHFLC strenthens the child's entire support network by supplying positive role models in the form of our staff - who receive regular training in child development, learning, and play - and by offering parenting and early childhood education programs to the family and general public.
